<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Maboroshi Tsukiyo is an adventure game released for the Dreamcast and Playstation consoles, in which the player takes the role of Takashi Tanaka (the player can choose another name) that one summer evenight he meet the ghost of a girl in the park, and the ghost girl start living with him in his appartment. The first night the girl appears to one of Takashi friends and the girl vanished after seeing the ghost, the ghost can enter other people's bodies too...
        		  <br><br>So that's when the adventure begins since after that the player will start meeting the different girls and the only gameplay is choosing between different answers that will lead the story in a way or another.
        		  <br><br>The game features different endings depending of the player choices during the game. The game features also japanese voice acting, unlockable CG galleries, character profiles, places stats and % of the advanced that the player had advanced in the game with each character.
        		  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Romance novel-style adventure game by going to proceed with the story of the hero action selection. Full-screen, developed in full voice, action hero, of course, various changes in the selection of a non-player characters no action hero. Iris encounter with the ghost girl, things will start to make a difference was a peaceful life ... until now.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Ghosts, Fantasy, Anime & Romance themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

